# Day 7 – Claude Model Selection & Reasoning Effort

## What I Learned

Today I learned that Claude provides different models for different types of work.
Choosing the right model and reasoning effort can improve both output quality and productivity.

---

## My Profile

- B.Tech CSE (AI & ML) Student
- Daily Claude User
- Learning AI and Prompt Engineering
- Interested in Coding, Research, and Career Growth

---

## My Personalized Claude Strategy

After analyzing my daily tasks, Claude suggested that Sonnet is the best model for most of my work.

### Haiku

I would use Haiku when I need:

- Quick answers
- Summaries
- Simple explanations
- Fast brainstorming

### Sonnet

I would use Sonnet for:

- Coding help
- Debugging
- Learning new concepts
- Creating GitHub documentation
- Resume and career-related work

This is the model I would use most often.

### Opus

I would use Opus for:

- Deep research
- Complex problem solving
- Long-term planning
- Advanced reasoning tasks

---

## Reasoning Effort Recommendations

### Low
For simple questions and quick responses.

### Standard
For daily learning, coding, and productivity tasks.

### High
For project planning, research, and detailed analysis.

### Max
For difficult problems that require deep thinking and multiple steps.

